            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "From what can be considered inline code, I changed to single backticks only for `True`, `False` and `None`. I did so because in all documentation double backticks used only 7 times for this things, while single backticks are used 27 times.\n\nOn the other hand, the Sphinx always uses double backticks for this things. An example can be found here: http://sphinx-doc.org/_sources/ext/autodoc.txt\n"
